==English==
===Etymology===
Old French [[feutre]], from mediæval Latin [[filtrum]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'fju:tə/

===Noun===
'''fewter'''
# a [[support]] or [[holder]] for a [[spear]], attached to a [[saddle]] or [[breastplate]]
#:*'''1994''': From heaven the spear-light vertical in its '''fewter'''. — Jeanette Winterson, ''Art & Lies''